\section{Introduction}

The P4P Portal Server provides applications information to better
utilize network resources.  This manual begins by discussing how to run the P4P Portal
Server, and then discusses how to configure the network information it provides to applications.

\subsection{Prerequisites}

Before reading this guide, you should be familiar with the P4P framework.  The
framework, including terminology and architecture, is discussed in:
\begin{verbatim}
http://p4p.cs.yale.edu/projects/p4p/draft-p4p-framework.txt
\end{verbatim}

This guide currently assumes you are running Linux, and that you have
installed at least the following P4P packages on your machine:
\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{p4p-portal-server}
\item \texttt{p4p-portal-shell}
\item \texttt{p4p-portal-utils}
\item \texttt{p4p-portal-docs}
\end{itemize}
